<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Great Britain/293:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1" type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-29T19:00:00+00:00">March
                                        29, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received March 29—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>122. Upon informal inquiry of Treasury official (Department’s 98,
                                December [<hi rend="italic">March</hi>] 26, 2 p.m.) I was informed
                                that with the <pb facs="0744" n="624" xml:id="pg_624"/> postponement
                                of the Lausanne Conference until June, Treasury had delayed
                                advisedly designating a representative and it was added informally
                                “should it not appear discourteous to the United States Government,
                                Treasury negotiations would be considerably aided if further delay
                                might be permitted until after Lausanne Conference.”</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>